#MEM id=ice-scoring-framework source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/nate/skills/custom/ice-scoring-framework/SKILL.md savings=1%
M||tx|---
M||name|ice-scoring-framework
M||desc|yv-calibrated ICE scoring for growth experiment prioritisation. Defines Impact, Confidence, and Effort scales anchored to nz and hb's business md. Load before scoring any experiment brief.
M||vers|1.0.0
M||tx|---
M|Purp|tx|ICE scoring w/o calibration is noise. "Impact 9" on a nz experiment means something specific — it moves purchase conversion. "Impact 9" on a hb experiment means something different — it moves trial-to-paid conversion. This skill anchors each dimension to yv's vt so scores are comparable across experiments and honest abt what they assume.
M|Purp|tx|---
M|ICE |tx|```
M|ICE |tx|ICE = (Impact + Confidence + Effort) / 3
M|ICE |tx|```
M|ICE |Each|10 = lowest effort (easiest to run).
M|ICE |**Pr|**
M|ICE |tx|\| ICE Score \| Action \|
M|ICE |tx|\|-----------\|--------\|
M|ICE |tx|\| ≥ 7.0 \| Fast track — run in current sprint \|
M|ICE |tx|\| 5.0–6.9 \| Queue — schedule in nx sprint \|
M|ICE |tx|\| 3.0–4.9 \| Backlog — revisit when higher-scored experiments are done \|
M|ICE |tx|\| < 3.0 \| Drop — effort exceeds expected return \|
M|ICE |tx|---
M|Impa|**No|**
M|Impa|tx|\| Score \| What it moves \|
M|Impa|tx|\|-------\|--------------\|
M|Impa|tx|\| 9–10 \| Directly increases purchase conversion rate or average order value \|
M|Impa|tx|\| 7–8 \| Increases add-to-cart rate or reduces cart abandonment \|
M|Impa|tx|\| 5–6 \| Increases pd page engagement (time on page, scroll depth) \|
M|Impa|tx|\| 3–4 \| Increases site traffic or sl engagement w/o direct conversion path \|
M|Impa|tx|\| 1–2 \| br awareness only — no measurable conversion signal within 14 days \|
M|Impa|**Ho|**
M|Impa|tx|\| Score \| What it moves \|
M|Impa|tx|\|-------\|--------------\|
M|Impa|tx|\| 9–10 \| Directly increases trial-to-paid conversion or reduces monthly churn \|
M|Impa|tx|\| 7–8 \| Increases activation rate (us reaching first key action within 7 days) \|
M|Impa|tx|\| 5–6 \| Increases trial signups from landing page \|
M|Impa|tx|\| 3–4 \| Increases traffic, leads, or trial starts w/o activation data \|
M|Impa|tx|\| 1–2 \| br awareness only — no measurable subscription signal within 14 days \|
M|Impa|tx|---
M|Conf|tx|\| Score \| Evidence basis \|
M|Conf|tx|\|-------\|---------------\|
M|Conf|tx|\| 9–10 \| 3+ comparable experiments w/ consistent results (own data) \|
M|Conf|tx|\| 7–8 \| 1–2 comparable experiments or strong analogous data from similar businesses \|
M|Conf|| 5–|us interviews, surveys, or sn recordings — no direct conversion data \|
M|Conf|tx|\| 3–4 \| Logical inference from related data (e.g., industry benchmarks, ka's tn data) \|
M|Conf|tx|\| 1–2 \| Pure hypothesis — no supporting evidence beyond intuition \|
M|Conf|**Ru|** Never round up Confidence. If evidence is thin, score it thin. A wrong hi-Confidence score burns 14 days on a bad bet.
M|Conf|tx|---
M|Effo|tx|\| Score \| Effort required \|
M|Effo|tx|\|-------\|----------------\|
M|Effo|tx|\| 9–10 \| < 1 day to im, nt or ln/ro executes w/o dv/rj \|
M|Effo|tx|\| 7–8 \| 1–3 days, single DRI can execute (no tc dependency) \|
M|Effo|tx|\| 5–6 \| 3–7 days, requires one dv/rj resource \|
M|Effo|tx|\| 3–4 \| 1–2 weeks, cross-team coordination required \|
M|Effo|tx|\| 1–2 \| > 2 weeks or major engineering lift \|
M|Effo|**Co|**
M|Effo|- "I|how long does a complete variant take?
M|Effo|- "I|what's the actual implementation time?
M|Effo|- "I|is it actually deployable in current state?
M|Effo|tx|---
M|Scor|For |
M|Scor|tx|```
M|Scor|Expe|[name]
M|Scor|Impa|[score] — assumes [specific outcome and which funnel stage]
M|Scor|Conf|[score] — based on [specific evidence or data source]
M|Scor|Effo|[score] — assumes [who executes, estimated time, dependencies]
M|Scor|ICE|[calculated average]
M|Scor|tx|```
M|Scor|**Ex|**
M|Scor|tx|```
M|Scor|Expe|Add size guide popup to nz PDP
M|Scor|Impa|7 — assumes reducing size uncertainty increases ATC rate by 10–15%
M|Scor|Conf|5 — based on 2 us interviews citing sizing as a hesitation; no split tst data
M|Scor|Effo|8 — mi estimated 2 days for ds + implementation
M|Scor|ICE|6.7 → Queue
M|Scor|tx|```
M|Scor|tx|---
M|ICE |Afte|
M|ICE |tx|\| If predicted Impact was... \| And actual was... \| up \|
M|ICE |tx|\|---------------------------\|------------------\|--------\|
M|ICE |tx|\| 8, actual 3 \| Overestimated \| Reduce confidence on similar hypotheses by 1–2 points \|
M|ICE |tx|\| 5, actual 8 \| Underestimated \| Increase priority of similar experiments; refine anchor definitions \|
M|ICE |tx|\| Consistent w/ prediction \| Well-calibrated \| No change needed \|
M|ICE |tx|A scoring md that consistently over- or under-predicts is the problem — not the experiments.